Japanese magazine ''Game Machine'' listed ''P-47: The Phantom Fighter'' on their June 15, 1988 issue as being the fourth most popular arcade game at the time.<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Game Machine's Best Hit Games 25 - テーブル型TVゲーム機 (Table Videos)|magazine={{ill|Game Machine|lt=Game Machine|ja|ゲームマシン}}|issue=334|publisher={{ill|Amusement Press, Inc.|lt=Amusement Press, Inc.|ja|アミューズメント通信社}}|date=15 June 1988|page=21|lang=ja}}</ref> The arcade version of ''P-47: The Phantom Fighter'' earned an "Annual Hit Game" award from ''Gamest'' magazine.<ref name="GM112p-47"/>

''[[Commodore User]]'' praised the addictive gameplay and graphics, stating that "this one looks set to be Jaleco's most successful product to date; it's certainly their best.".<ref name="CUserARCp-47">{{cite magazine|url=https://archive.org/stream/commodore-user-magazine-59#page/n97/mode/1up|title=Arcade: P-47 - Jaleco (2 x 10p)|magazine=[[Commodore User]]|issue=59|publisher=[[EMAP]]|date=August 1988|page=98}}</ref> ''[[Computer and Video Games]]''{{'}} Clare Edgeley commended the graphics and regarded the game as "well worth playing."<ref name="CVGARCp-47">{{cite magazine|last=Edgeley|first=Clare|url=https://archive.org/stream/cvg-magazine-082#page/n105/mode/1up|title=Arcade Action - Arcade Round-Up!|magazine=[[Computer and Video Games]]|issue=82|publisher=[[EMAP]]|date=August 1988|page=106}}</ref> ''[[The Games Machine]]''{{'}}s Robin Hogg and Cameron Pound commended the fun and addictive gameplay despite the standard graphics and sound.<ref name="TGMARCp-47">{{cite magazine|last1=Hogg|first1=Robin|last2=Pound|first2=Cameron|url=https://archive.org/stream/the-games-machine-09#page/n79/mode/1up|title=Confrontation: Coin-Op - P47 Freedom Fighter|magazine=[[The Games Machine]]|issue=9|publisher=[[Newsfield Publications]]|date=August 1988|page=80}}</ref> ''[[Your Sinclair]]''{{'}}s Ciarán Brennan regarded the title to be a poor ''[[Gradius (video game)|Nemesis]]'' variant lacking speed and complexity, criticizing the low difficulty and uninspired sprites, stating that "this is definitely one for the fanatic."<ref name="YSARCp-47">{{cite magazine|last=Brennan|first=Ciarán|url=https://archive.org/stream/your-sinclair-32#page/n62/mode/1up|title=Slots Of Fun: P47|magazine=[[Your Sinclair]]|issue=32|publisher=[[Dennis Publishing]]|date=August 1988|page=63}}</ref>

''[[Crash (magazine)|Crash]]''{{'}}s Philip King and Mark Caswell regarded the presentation to be mediocre and the gameplay to be unoriginal but addictive, stating that "once you start blasting away, you'll find it hard to stop."<ref name="CrashARCp-47">{{cite magazine|last1=King|first1=Philip|last2=Caswell|first2=Mark|url=https://archive.org/stream/crash-magazine-57#page/n75/mode/1up|title=Arcade Action: P47 Freedom Fighter (Jaleco)|magazine=[[Crash (magazine)|Crash]]|issue=57|publisher=[[Newsfield Publications]]|date=October 1988|page=76}}</ref> ''[[ACE (magazine)|ACE]]''{{'}}s Andy Smith stated that "the game's fun but it's not going to get your heart racing too much."<ref name="ACEARCp-47">{{cite magazine|last=Smith|first=Andy|url=https://archive.org/stream/ACE_Issue_14_1988-11_Future_Publishing_GB#page/n84/mode/1up|title=Arcades - Extended Play: P47 (Jaleco 30p)|magazine=[[ACE (magazine)|ACE]]|issue=14|publisher=[[Future Publishing]]|date=November 1988|page=85}}</ref> Boris Schneider-Johne of German publication ''Power Play'' commended the visuals and bosses, though the slowdown when many sprites are on-screen was criticized but noted this was crucial for certain situations, stating that "if you want to let off steam for a few laps, "''P-47''" is just the thing. But if you are not a real action fan, the blast of air becomes too monotonous after half an hour at the latest."<ref name="PPARCp-47">{{cite magazine|last=Schneider-Johne|first=Boris|url=https://archive.org/stream/Power.Play.N09.1988.12-KCz#page/n74/mode/1up|title=Power Automatenspiele: P-47|magazine={{ill|Power Play (magazine)|lt=Power Play|de|Power Play (Zeitschrift)}}|issue=9|publisher=[[Future plc]]|date=December 1988|page=75|lang=de}}</ref>

